No priority for online orders placed through their mobile app. Example: I placed an online order for 11:25 yesterday and ended up arriving into the store a few minutes after my time. I thought this would be no big deal considering once they complete the order they just place it on the shelf with all of the other online orders. This however was not the case, nor has it been the last several times I've visited this location. I had to wait 15 minutes in the store, which at the current time was the entire length of the in store line at the time to receive my sandwich. This happened to me multiple times a few months back and I stopped going to this location. I tried to give this location another chance yesterday and I ended up with the same experience. The food is great but the reason for low review is because of the customer service and how dirty the place is. I came in at a slow time to get a chicken sandwich. I went up to go place my order and the young lady didn't even greet me or told me someone will be right with me. She left and came back and asked what I wanted. Mind you it is only 3:30pm on a slow Sunday. I told her a grill chicken sandwich and went on from there, I went to go pay and the cashier was really nice and showed good customer service. I went back to tell her my toppings. And, the cashier told her that it was a chicken sandwich. Than she turned to me with an angry expression and said "I am going to remake your sandwich again" and I agreed. I thought maybe she didn't hear me or I said it wrong, who knows no big deal. But! What really got me upset was she turned to her coworker and said "She said grilled cheese sandwich right, I know I am crazy!" Uhm.... For one I did not say you were, and two if I made a mistake let me know in a kind way and no big deal. Instead of having an attitude problem and whispering underneath your breath. I feel sorry for the employees that have to work with her. But, the rest of the team is great tho! They just need to clean up more.

The food is like any other Pot Belly's,  but at this location sometimes the service is excruciatingly slow.  With no one else in line,  sometimes it takes minutes before someone takes my order.  Everything is just so slow,  and that can be a big deal if you're trying to catch VRE train.

I got the cheese sub and It was okay. My banana and vanilla smoothie on the other hand was AMAZING! I like the location and seating options but I wasn't impressed by the fact that my pick up sub order wasn't ready and I had to wait an additional 15 minutes for my food.

I like this sandwich shop.  Not a very rich menu but what it has is pretty good.  I do love the ice cream shakes and the smoothies, I think they're one of the best. Sandwiches are great but in my opinion too small, lol I guess i'm just greedy. I have eaten at this chain many times before and all locations are pretty much the same.  I normally go there for the strawberry shakes. They have an X-Large size which many other places do not. This is good for those hot summer days when you just crave something cold and lots of it. The shakes have lots of real fruit chunks in it which adds to the treat.  The atmosphere in every Potbelly spot i've been in is good to sit down in. The staff is always happy and courteous. I recommend this place for a quick spot to eat.

This is our go-to spot when ordering lunch for our job. Sandwiches are well made and prices are great for this area. Boxed lunch withe sandwich, chips, and cookie for $7/pp is a steal. This includes all the condiments, plates, plastic ware, and napkins. Our order is always correct, but I would recommend you request you food earlier than you would like to pick it up because we always end up waiting a good 15 minutes longer.
